  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Special Account for IHP Fund for the Implementation of SDG 6</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sound, science based, water resources management, is indispensable for advancing sustainable development and has been acknowledged by the 2030 Development Agenda through the establishment of a dedicated goal, SDG 6. In accordance with Resolution XXII-7 adopted by the 22nd IHP Council,(June 2016) the Fund will receive financial support enabling UNESCO to &quot;take actions at the request of the Member States for capacity-building activities in support of Member States for the implementation of the SDG 6 and other water related goals&quot;, including thus other targets such as 11.5, 13.1 and 13.3 (the last two focusing on climate change), which are directly linked to SDG 6.</narrative>
  </description>
